About Lionbridge

Management Team






John Fennelly
Chief Executive Officer
Prior to Lionbridge, Mr. John Fennelly served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at HireRight. Mr. Fennelly has more than 30 years of operational management and human resources technology experience.
Learn More

Rich Tobin
COO, Global Language & Translation
Tobin is Senior Vice President and General Manager, responsible for the operations of Lionbridge’s Global Language & Translation business. He joined Lionbridge in September 2013 from DigitasLBi, an integrated global brand agency.
Learn More

Marc Osofsky
COO, Global Offerings
Osofsky manages a $100MM P&L which includes the company’s fastest growing technology and productized service businesses including all of the Company’s commercial SaaS products, ecommerce, crowdsourcing and APIs. Osofsky has more than 20 years of experience developing high growth products and high performance product management, marketing and sales teams to execute.
Learn More

Clemente Cohen
Chief Financial Officer
Cohen leads the Lionbridge global finance organization and is responsible for the worldwide accounting, financial reporting, tax, treasury, financial planning & analysis, risk management and financial control activities of the company.  He most recently was the CFO of Empirix, where he was responsible for a broad range of functions including Finance, Legal, Operations, Treasury, Accounting, and IT/Corporate Applications across 10 countries.
Learn More

Clint Poole
Chief Marketing Officer and Senior Vice President
As Senior Vice President and Chief Marketing Officer for Lionbridge, Clint leads all aspects of the company’s global go-to-market strategy, demand generation, and branding initiatives. He joined the company in 2012, bringing over a decade of experience in developing and enhancing brands and improving marketing performance to drive revenue growth for private and publically traded professional services companies.
Learn More

Ann Lazarus-Barnes
Senior Vice President, Human Resources
Ann Lazarus-Barnes is responsible for leading the human capital programs and processes that support Lionbridge’s organization and strategic goals. Ann joined Lionbridge in April, 2016. Prior to joining Lionbridge, Ann was the Vice President, Human Resources Business Partner at Ascend Learning, a technology education company located in Burlington, MA.
Learn More

Peggy Shukur
Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary
Shukur is responsible for Lionbridge’s worldwide legal affairs and manages its legal department, in addition to serving as Secretary to its Board of Directors. Prior to joining Lionbridge in 2000 as the Company’s first General Counsel, Shukur served as Senior Securities Counsel for Oak Industries, a $500 million NYSE company, through its acquisition by Corning in 2000, and as Senior Attorney at Digital Equipment Corporation, through its acquisition by Compaq in 1998.
Learn More

Sara Buda
SVP, Corporate Development and Strategic Planning
Buda manages Lionbridge’s corporate development and strategic business planning. In this role she leads the Company’s mergers and acquisitions activities, oversees the development of business plans for the Company’s business units and manages integration and strategic business change initiatives.  Buda also oversees external and internal communications.
Learn More












