5 External links



History[edit]
The company was founded in 1996.[5] In 2005, they acquired Bowne Global Solutions, then the largest localization provider[clarification needed] worldwide.[6][7] They acquired Darwin Zone, a digital marketing services agency based in Costa Rica, and Clay Tablet Technologies, a content connectivity[clarification needed] software firm, in 2014.[8][9]
In 2015, they acquired Zurich-based CLS Communication, a translation solutions[clarification needed] provider, and Geotext, a legal translation company.[10][11][12][13] In December 2016, it was announced that Lionbridge entered into a definitive agreement to be acquired by H.I.G. Capital.[14] The deal was announced closed in May, 2017.[15]





